<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="362" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,898,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,934,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[333,431,934,958]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Ferkeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[333,431,934,958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Ferkeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its gamma 
<typeStatus box="[808,856,935,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">type</typeStatus>
dorsal scutum (
<figureCitation box="[1050,1121,934,959]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,231,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ferkeria spp., in dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. A, male holotype, B, female (CBN); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Fig. 
<number box="[1108,1121,935,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); anterior scutal area with moderately elevated frontal hump and high lateral tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[871,953,970,995]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1325,1347]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,222,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1301]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Ferkeria spp., males in lateral and ventral view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. holotype, A, ventral, B, lateral; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, ventral, D, lateral. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Figs. 
<number box="[939,953,971,995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B and 
<number box="[1036,1051,971,995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="2.0">2</number>
D); tuberculate and dome-shaped ocularium, with a pair of large tubercles; densely tuberculate carapace; lateral scutal margins with prominent tubercles; unconspicuous scutal grooves; scutal areas I–IV each with a pair of tubercles (enlarged and spiniform on area IV); yellow patches on the sides of the carapace, reaching as far as the scutal area IV (
<figureCitation box="[1232,1312,1078,1103]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,231,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ferkeria spp., in dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. A, male holotype, B, female (CBN); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1330,1344,1079,1103]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1733,1755]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,375,1709]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,375,1709]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ferkeria spp., specimens preserved in ethanol, dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov., A, male holotype, B, female (CNB); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243760/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">8</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1405,1421,1079,1103]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1556]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,700,1557]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ferkeria spp., live specimens: F. flavicoxae sp. nov., A, male, B, female; F. vestita, C, male, D, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243761/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<number box="[1405,1421,1079,1103]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
); posterior scutal margin with pair of prominent spines curved posteriorly; free tergites I–III with a row of tubercles; median extremity of anal operculum with a large pair of tubercles; isomorphic chelicerae in both sexes, tuberculate bulla (
<figureCitation box="[223,301,1186,1211]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,231,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ferkeria spp., in dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. A, male holotype, B, female (CBN); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[316,330,1187,1211]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1325,1347]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,222,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1301]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Ferkeria spp., males in lateral and ventral view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. holotype, A, ventral, B, lateral; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, ventral, D, lateral. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">2</figureCitation>
B and 
<number box="[404,419,1187,1211]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="2.0">2</number>
D); pedipalpal femur with dorsal tubercles and a prominent row of ventral tubercles (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,569,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,569,1853]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ferkeria spp. pedipalp of males in lateral view (femur – tarsus) and in detail of tibia and tarsus, respectively: A, B, F. flavicoxae sp. nov. (MZUSP 67893); C, D, F. vestita (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243757/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,164,1222,1247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A and 
<number box="[241,255,1222,1247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="5.0">5</number>
C); wide, dimorphic coxa IV (large in male), reaching the posterior scutal margin, tuberculate and with a prolateral apical apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[467,532,1258,1283]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,231,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ferkeria spp., in dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. A, male holotype, B, female (CBN); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Fig. 
<number box="[519,532,1259,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); femur IV dorsally curved; femora–metatarsi I–IV covered with thick tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1294,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1453,1475]" captionTargetBox="[164,1415,389,1412]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1428]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ferkeria spp., male leg IV (trochanter – patella) in dorsal and ventral views: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. holotype, A, dorsal, B, ventral; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, dorsal, D, ventral. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243755/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,227,1295,1319]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); male’s basitarsi I and III dimorphic, enlarged; leg tarsi III and IV smooth; penis without dorsal process of glans, dorsally wrinkled glans base, stylus with gonopore and keels placed on apex, without ventral apical keels and ventral apice of the truncus with two pairs of small macrosetae group B (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1092,1366,1391]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1983,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,683,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,673,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ferkeria spp., penis in dorsal and ventral views: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. (MZUSP 67893) A, dorsal, B, ventral; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, dorsal, D, ventral. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (A, B) and 0.05 mm (C, D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243758/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Figs. 
<number box="[1078,1092,1366,1391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1146,1162,1367,1391]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1863,1885]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,555,1839]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ferkeria spp., lateral view of penis and stylus: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. (MZUSP 67893) A, lateral, B, stylus; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, lateral, D, stylus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (A), 0.05 mm (C) and 0.01 mm (B and D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243759/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<number box="[1146,1162,1367,1391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,898,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,715,1402,1427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Comparison with other cosmetid genera.</emphasis>
The cosmetids have the most convoluted taxonomy within Gonyleptoidea. The relationships of its genera are obscure, since the Roewerian system is still dominant and no comprehensive phylogeny is available for the group. 
<taxonomicName box="[752,850,1475,1499]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Ferkeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[752,850,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Ferkeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1192,1352,1475,1499]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Acantholibitia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1192,1352,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Acantholibitia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mello- 
<bibRefCitation author="Leitao" box="[151,298,1510,1535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. de (1928) Opilioes de Matto Grosso e Pernambuco. Boletim do Museu Nacional, 4 (2), 9 - 13." type="journal article" year="1928">
