, 
<taxonomicName authority="Roewer, 1917" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1917" box="[330,626,1547,1571]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Proerginus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[330,454,1547,1570]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Proerginus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer" box="[466,626,1547,1571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1917) 52 neue Opilioniden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 82 (2), 90 - 158." type="journal article" year="1917">
Roewer, 
<number box="[570,626,1547,1571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="1917.0">1917</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1879" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1879" box="[690,945,1546,1571]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Vonones" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[690,783,1547,1570]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Vonones</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Simon" box="[795,945,1546,1571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" refString="Simon, E. (1879) Essai d'une classification des Opiliones Mecostethi. Remarques synonymiques et descriptions d'especes nouvelles. Premiere partie. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 22, 183 - 241." type="journal article" year="1879">
Simon, 
<number box="[886,945,1547,1571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="1879.0">1879</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by having the gamma 
<typeStatus box="[1229,1277,1547,1571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">type</typeStatus>
scutal shape, frontal hump of dorsal scutum elevated and tuberculate (except 
<taxonomicName authority="Roewer, 1947" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1947" box="[878,1316,1582,1607]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Libitiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianum">
<emphasis box="[878,1146,1582,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Libitiosoma bolivianum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer" box="[1154,1316,1583,1607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1947) Diagnosen neuer Gattungen und Arten der Opiliones Laniatores. Weitere Weberknechte XII. Cosmetidae. Senckenbergiana, 28 (1 - 3), 1 - 58." type="journal article" year="1947">
Roewer, 
<number box="[1256,1316,1583,1607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="1947.0">1947</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), posterior scutal margin and free tergites with a row of tubercles, coxa I with prominent prolateral apophysis, coxa IV with a large prolateral apical apophysis, and isomorphic chelicerae (except in 
<taxonomicName box="[1029,1153,1655,1678]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Proerginus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1153,1655,1678]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Proerginus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Two features, shared exclusively with 
<taxonomicName box="[346,483,1691,1715]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Platygyndes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[346,483,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Platygyndes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, seem to relate both genera, the dome-shaped ocularium and dorsally-visible, wide coxa IV in males. However, we view this relationship with caution since the morphology of the family is poorly known. 
<taxonomicName box="[241,339,1763,1787]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Ferkeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[241,339,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Ferkeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all of the afore mentioned genera mostly by its non-flattened dorsal scutal areas, each with paired tubercles progressively enlarged towards the posterior margin. There are some notable characters on the morphology of the penis in 
<taxonomicName box="[508,606,1835,1859]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Ferkeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[508,606,1835,1859]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Ferkeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as the two pairs of small, apical macrosetae group B on the ventral truncus, which differs from other genera within the family that have just one pair or none; the stylus with gonopore and keels placed on its apex, known only on genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Roewer, 1917" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1917" box="[754,1033,1907,1931]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Sibambea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,864,1907,1931]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Sibambea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer" box="[874,1033,1907,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1917) 52 neue Opilioniden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 82 (2), 90 - 158." type="journal article" year="1917">
Roewer, 
<number box="[977,1033,1907,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="1917.0">1917</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see figure 
<number box="[1174,1188,1906,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="6.0">6</number>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kury" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" refString="Kury, A. B. &amp; Villarreal, M. O. (2015) The prickly blade mapped: establishing homologies and a chaetotaxy for macrosetae of penis ventral plate in Gonyleptoidea (Arachnida, Opiliones, Laniatores). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 174 (1), 1 - 46. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12225" type="journal article" year="2015">
Kury &amp; Villarreal 
<number box="[151,212,1942,1967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="2015.0">2015</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); the glans with sac wrinkled on its dorsal face, contrasted with the other known genera were it is smooth dorsally.
</paragraph>
